-- Axis Said to Plan Sale of 5 1/2-Year Dollar-Denominated Benchmark Bonds
-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s
-- 2010-10-26T02:01:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/axis-said-to-plan-sale-of-5-1-2-year-dollar-denominated-benchmark-bonds.html
Axis Bank Ltd. plans to sell 5 1/2-
year dollar bonds at a spread of 362.5 basis points to 375 basis
points, according to a person familiar with the matter.  The benchmark sale may price as early as today, the person
said, asking not to be identified as details are private.
Benchmark typically means at least $500 million.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Katrina Nicholas at 
 knicholas2@bloomberg.net  